default10
default.
default              
defaultA working group has recently been established by the Department for Education (
defaultDfE
default) to review the qualifications fra
defaultmework for residential home staff. Currently, there are significant numbers of staff who have not achieved the basic NVQ Level 3 qualification to work with children and young people. This has led to a workforce who feels unprepared for dealing with the mos
defaultt challenging of behaviours, and young people who are not managed appropriately, leading to high numbers of placement breakdown and higher arrest and conviction rates. The YJB is a member of the working group, and is working with 
defaultDfE
default to ensure that the qua
defaultlifications framework includes a clear and explicit focus on the needs of children and young people in the youth justice system. 
default11
default.
default              
defaultCurrently, young people completing a community order while they are in care do not receive the same level of support as yo
defaultung people living with their parents. This leads to higher than average breach rates
default, which then creates further convictions and an increased risk of a custodial sentence. As part of the qualifications framework review, the YJB would recommend that there 
defaultis a specific module focusing on the youth justice system, to raise awareness of the implications of failure to provide the appropriate support.  A working protocol between the local youth offending team and residential placement which outlines roles and r
defaultesponsibilities of respective members of staff would further support improvements in practice.
